      "title": "Copy SSH Keys to Server",
      "text": "Here we describe how to copy over your public ssh keys to a server on Linux and MacOS."
    },
    {
      "type": "html",
      "id": "4405a8f93edd25ed",
      "text": "<H3>Use ssh-copy-id"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "7cbf63f4b6887043",
      "text": "After generating an SSH key pair, you will want to copy your public key to your new server. We will cover two easy ways to do this."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "bf59a2880d25e5b5",
      "text": "If your local machine has the [[ssh-copy-id]] script installed, you can use it to install your public key to any user that you have login credentials for."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "6800db28e7d34f6d",
      "text": "Run the [[ssh-copy-id]] script by specifying the user and IP address of the server that you want to install the key on, like this:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "32206e2b217df192",
      "text": "ssh-copy-id -i demo demo@SERVER_IP_ADDRESS"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d2cddb460e941ead",
      "text": "You only need to pass the \"-i demo\" parameter if you are generating a second ssh key. If you only have one you can leave this empty and simply issue:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "a6efd50b28db6dd7",
      "text": "ssh-copy-id username@SERVER_IP_ADDRESS"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d57a70e8968c7b24",
      "text": "However in our case we are assuming you have just set up a server and generated and used an ssh key for the \"root\" user to gain initial access. The second \"demo\" key being specified is for the \"demo\" user you just created and had given sudo permissions. So you have two keys and need to specify which one to upload with the \"i\" parameter."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f71c1bcff6e830d8",
      "text": "After providing your password at the prompt, your public key will be added to the remote user's .ssh/authorized_keys file. The corresponding private key can now be used to log into the server."
    },
